** The system successfully initiates the pre-authorization process, receives an approval ID, and stores it in the patient's billing record.\n\n**Test Case 3: Notification for Non-Covered Tests**\n\n* **Test Case ID:** HC-311-TC-03\n* **Objective:** To verify that the system notifies the billing coordinator and patient when a test is not covered and offers alternative payment options.\n* **Preconditions:**\n\t+ Patient is scheduled for a radiology test that is not covered by their insurance.\n\t+ Insurance provider API indicates that the test is not covered.\n* **Steps:**\n\t1. Log in as a billing coordinator.\n\t2. Select a patient scheduled for a radiology test that is not covered by their insurance.\n\t3. Click on \"Schedule Test\".\n\t4. Verify that the system sends a notification to the billing coordinator and patient indicating that the test is not covered.\n\t5. Verify that the notification includes alternative payment options.\n* **Expected Result:** The system successfully notifies the billing coordinator and patient, and offers alternative payment options.\n\n**Test Case 4: Error Handling for Insurance API Unavailability**\n\n* **Test Case ID:** HC-311-TC-04\n* **Objective:** To verify that the system handles errors when the insurance provider API is unavailable.\n* **Preconditions:**\n\t+ Insurance provider API is unavailable.\n* **Steps:**\n\t1. Log in as a billing coordinator.\n\t2. Select a patient scheduled for a radiology test.\n\t3. Click on \"Schedule Test\".\n\t4. Verify that the system displays an error message indicating that the insurance provider API is unavailable.\n\t5. Verify that the system provides instructions for retrying the API call or contacting support.\n* **Expected Result:** The system successfully handles the error and provides guidance for resolving the issue.\n\n**Test Case 5: Negative Testing for Invalid Patient or Test Information**\n\n* **Test Case ID:** HC-311-TC-05\n* **Objective:** To verify that the system handles invalid